    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Dictionary",
        "",
        "Can be created via fromEntries and via literal syntax. New creates an empty dict. Both NSDictionary and NSMutableDicitionray are supported or anything responding to initWithObjects:forKeys:count: or initWithObjects:forKeys: .<br.>",
        "Supports dict[customOrStringKey] lookup.<br>",
        "Normal property access also works, but get prefers normal properties. Methods might be hidden."
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as objc from \"system://objc\"",
        "const NSDict = objc.class.NSDictionary;",
        "const NSMutDict = objc.class.NSMutableDictionary;",
        "{}",
        "const d = NSDict.fromEntries(#{kutya: 42, faja:0, [1000]: \"ezer\"});",
        "$log(d[\"kutya\"], d.kutya, d[\"faja\"], d[1000]);",
        "NSDict d2 { alma= \"golden\"; korte= \"vilmos\"};",
        "$log(d2[\"alma\"], d2[\"korte\"]);",
        "NSMutDict d3 { alma= \"golden\"; korte= \"vilmos\"};",
        "d3.alma=\"jonatan\";",
        "d3.kukac=10;",
        "d3[42]=11;",
        "$log(d3.alma, d3.kukac, d3[42]);",
        ""
      ]
    },
