    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Test and notes",
        "",
        "### Memory management",
        "",
        "By convention all methods starting with `new`, `alloc`, `copy` or `mutableCopy` returns a new reference. Method call should act accordingly. Such methods should be never a property (so alloc and new must be called always).",
        "",
        "So all the calls below is expected to log no more box to the stdout (via NSLog). Probably there should be a proper test for this."
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as objc from \"system://objc\"",
        "const Box = objc.class.Box;",
        "{}",
        "$log((new Box).retainCount); // must be 1 ",
        " //new, alloc must not be a property but a method, should log 1",
        "$log(Box.new().retainCount);",
        "$log(Box.alloc().retainCount); // no constructor (init) called so only logs no more box",
        "$log((new Box).copy().retainCount);"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as objc from \"system://objc\"",
        "{}",
        "//objc.makeBlock_vBNSError(()=>{});",
        "$log(objc.class.Box.callBlock(objc.makeBlock(\"i12@?0i8\", v => 2*v), 21));",
        "$log(objc.makeBlock(\"i12@?0i8\", v=>2*v)(21));"
      ]
    },
