    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Protocols",
        "",
        "* protocols are represented special objects (ObjcProto)",
        "* `getProtocol(name)` module function returns the protocol by name",
        "* `protocolsOf(objOrClassOrName)` module function returns (multiretval) the protocols implemented by the class of the param",
        "* ObjcProto cached methods (todo: invalidate later)",
        "```js",
        "interface ObjcProto {",
        "    methods() { /* #{name:selector, type:encodecType, isOptional:true}, ...*/} // multiple return value of methods",
        "    staticMethods() { /*format as for methods()*/ } // the non-istnace methods of protocol",
        "    uncachedMethods(isRequired=true, isInstance=true) { /*queries method */}",
        "}",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as objc from \"system://objc\";",
        "dumpProto(log, prot) {",
        "    if (!prot) return;",
        "    log(prot.name);",
        "    map(log, prot.methods());",
        "    log('static');",
        "    map(log, prot.staticMethods());",
        "}",
        "dumpProtocolsOf(log, objOrClass) {",
        "    map(dumpProto(log,?), objc.protocolsOf(objOrClass))",
        "}",
        "{}",
        "dumpProtocolsOf($log,objc.class.NSString);",
        "//dumpProtocolsOf($log,objc.class.NSObject);",
        "//dumpProtocolsOf($log,objc.class.NSArray); // no protocol with objectAtIndex "
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "{}",
        "//dumpProto($log, objc.getProtocol(\"NSObject\"));",
        "//dumpProto($log, objc.getProtocol(\"NSFastEnumerator\"));",
        "dumpProto($log, objc.getProtocol(\"Babbal\"));"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Implementing objc objects/classes",
        "",
        "Objc calling needs selectors and corresponding signatures. Therefore an nng object needs some kind of descriptor for this.",
        "",
        "Note: the alternative to query signatures on demand doesn't work so well since there might be a lot of queries and it might need crossing threadboundaries",
        "",
        "An object needs a class descriptor that can be created via the ClassDesc constructor (it is a callable constructor). Methods can be added to descriptors. When a descriptor creation has been finished build creates a descriptor. Descriptor can assigned to multiple objects.",
        "",
        "Note: technically build() merely finalizes descriptor and returns itself. However, in the future build might return a new object. The descriptor is considered immutable after built.",
        "",
        "When exporting an object to objc its `_objcDescriptor` property is queried for the class descriptor. A simple way to share descriptor with class instances is to define a getter returning the descriptor."
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as objc from \"system://objc\"",
        "import {@objcProto} from \"uie/darwin/objc_support.xs\"",
        "const NSArray = objc.class.NSArray;",
        "const TestMetaClass = objc.ClassDesc(/*basedesc*/)",
        "          /*.base(baseDesc)",
        "          .import(otherDesc)",
        "          .import(proto) // objc proto",
        "          .importClassSig(sig)",
        "          .importFromClass()",
        "          .setBlockSig()*/",
        "          .setProperty(@korte, \"i\")",
        "          .addMethod(\"alma\", '*@:')",
        "          .setMethod(\"setAlma:\", \"v@:*\", @setAlma)",
        "          .addMethod(\"call:withInt:\", 'i@:@\"(i@?i)\"i')",
        "          .build();",
        "{}",
        "@objcProto(TestMetaClass)",
        "class Test {",
        "  korte = 42;",
        "  alma() { this.#alma };",
        "  setAlma(s) { this.#alma = \"new \" + s }",
        "  #alma=\"alma\";",
        "  call(f, i) { f(i) }",
        "}",
        "@objcProto(TestMetaClass)",
        "object test {",
        "  korte = 42;",
        "  a=\"proba\";",
        "  #x = \"alma\";",
        "  alma() { this.#x };",
        "  setAlma(s) { this.#x = \"new \" + s }",
        "  call_withInt(f, i) { f(i) }",
        "}",
        "",
        "const to = objc.toObj(test);",
        "{}",
        "//$log(test[objc.objDescriptor]);",
        "$log(to == objc.toObj(test));",
        "$log(to.a, ??to.alma, to.korte);",
        "to.alma = \"value\";",
        "$log(??to.alma);",
        "$log(to.call_withInt_(v=>2*v, 21));",
        "$log(objc.toObj(new Test).call(v=>3*v, 14));",
        "//$log(tob.b);",
        "NSArray arr[to];",
        "arr[0];"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {objDescriptor} from \"system://objc\"",
        "{}",
        "objDescriptor"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Some function return error in outargs.",
        "",
        "If no argument is gven a null or it is undef, a null pointer is passed to the method. The method might or might not accept this.",
        "",
        "`outarg` and `outerr` symbolc can be used in place of outargs with slightly different semantics. In the opinion of the author the `outerr` produces the most convenient results for common error handling",
        "",
        "`outerr`",
        "* if the error outarg is kept null only the main return value is returned",
        "* if the error is filled the main return value is ignored if it is coverted to false or undedf (null object, null string)",
        "* otherwise, the first return value is the error and the second is the main return value",
        "",
        "`outarg`",
        "* always multiretval, the first retval is the return value of the function and the second retval is the outarg",
        "* e.g `const ret,outVal = obj.method(..., @objc.outarg)`"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as objc from \"system://objc\"",
        "const NSString = objc.class.NSString;",
        "{}",
        "// outarg, outerr with error and false retval",
        "$log(??objc.class.NSFileManager.defaultManager.moveItemAtPath(\"alma\", 'kortef', objc.outarg));",
        "$log(??objc.class.NSFileManager.defaultManager.moveItemAtPath(\"alma\", 'kortef', objc.outerr));",
        "// outarg, outerr, undef on success",
        "$log(NSString.initWithContentsOfFile(\"/Users/beaver/lokutya\",4,objc.outerr));",
